Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine in both serum and blood, indicating significant renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting nephrotic syndrome or advanced kidney disease. Hemoglobin is elevated, possibly due to hemoconcentration. HbA1c is low, ruling out chronic hyperglycemia. Immediate nephrology evaluation is recommended.
